select `name`, `payload` from `settings` where `group` = 'general'
select * from `users` where `id` = '0125f749-8253-4641-b6d7-b4bb7ccb1459' limit 1

select `master_assets_condition`.`name`, count(assets.id) as total from `assets` inner join `master_assets_condition` on `assets`.`condition_id` = `master_assets_condition`.`id` group by `master_assets_condition`.`name`, `master_assets_condition`.`id`

select `master_assets_category`.`name`, count(assets.id) as total from `assets` inner join `master_assets_category` on `assets`.`category_id` = `master_assets_category`.`id` group by `master_assets_category`.`name`, `master_assets_category`.`id`

select `master_assets_transaction_status`.`name`, count(assets_mutation.id) as total from `assets_mutation` inner join `master_assets_transaction_status` on `assets_mutation`.`transaction_status_id` = `master_assets_transaction_status`.`id` group by `master_assets_transaction_status`.`name`, `master_assets_transaction_status`.`id`
select count(*) as aggregate from `assets_mutation`

select `master_assets_locations`.`name`, count(assets.id) as total from `assets` left join `assets_mutation` on `assets`.`id` = `assets_mutation`.`assets_id` and assets_mutation.id = (SELECT id FROM assets_mutation WHERE assets_id = assets.id ORDER BY mutation_date DESC LIMIT 1) left join `master_assets_locations` on `assets_mutation`.`location_id` = `master_assets_locations`.`id` group by `master_assets_locations`.`name`
select count(*) as aggregate from `assets`
